1
00:00:35,577 --> 00:00:37,579
Wait, hold on. I don't get it.

2
00:00:38,121 --> 00:00:39,414
Why are you helping us?

3
00:00:39,497 --> 00:00:43,084
<i>Didn't La Morte Bianca send you</i>
<i>to kill me and Chiara?</i>

4
00:00:48,339 --> 00:00:49,674
Oh wait.

5
00:00:49,758 --> 00:00:52,969
Aren't you with someone?
Is this solo travel?

6
00:00:53,052 --> 00:00:54,512
Oh no, Auntie.

7
00:00:54,596 --> 00:00:56,848
I'm with someone.
Actually, he's on his way here.

8
00:00:56,931 --> 00:00:59,642
<i>He said he'll text me once he arrived.</i>

9
00:00:59,726 --> 00:01:03,354
What if Agent Alex can get Mikoy back?

10
00:01:03,438 --> 00:01:04,522
That's not going to happen.

11
00:01:04,606 --> 00:01:05,607
Why?

12
00:01:05,690 --> 00:01:08,902
Because that fool is so in love,

13
00:01:14,365 --> 00:01:17,869
And when we think about it,
the world will be a better place

14
00:01:18,453 --> 00:01:19,913
without all of you.

15
00:01:23,792 --> 00:01:25,001
What are you waiting for?

16
00:01:44,437 --> 00:01:45,563
What's this?

17
00:01:46,105 --> 00:01:47,607
A bribe?

18
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:51,111
What I want is a suitcase.

19
00:01:51,903 --> 00:01:53,363
Hey, that's ilegal.

20
00:01:53,446 --> 00:01:56,449
And I'm just a lowly employee.

21
00:01:56,533 --> 00:01:58,284
What are you thinking?

22
00:01:58,368 --> 00:02:01,121
What I mean by suitcase is,
like, pack my luggage,

23
00:02:01,204 --> 00:02:03,123
so I can follow to Hong Kong right away.

24
00:02:03,873 --> 00:02:04,833
Oh dear.

25
00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:08,545
Even if I pack five suitcases for you,

26
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:11,339
it wouldn't do any good
because what you need

27
00:02:11,422 --> 00:02:13,216
is a round-trip plane ticket,

28
00:02:13,299 --> 00:02:15,385
which I cannot afford.

29
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:18,054
Okay, fine.

30
00:02:29,399 --> 00:02:31,359
If you don't believe us either,

31
00:02:31,442 --> 00:02:33,027
then just shoot us.

32
00:02:33,111 --> 00:02:34,988
Or just call the police,

33
00:02:35,071 --> 00:02:36,406
instead of us standing here

34
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,241
when nothing was happening anyway.

35
00:03:10,982 --> 00:03:12,317
Yes, I'll be back.

36
00:03:25,663 --> 00:03:27,498
Sorry because…

37
00:03:27,582 --> 00:03:29,834
I was so snappy earlier.

38
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:31,502
You were being so persistent.

39
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:33,338
Not even a minute had passed and then,

40
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:35,423
you started asking me about Agent Alex.

41
00:03:36,132 --> 00:03:37,133
Was that right?

42
00:03:38,384 --> 00:03:40,511
I thought you were apologizing to me?

43
00:03:40,595 --> 00:03:41,888
Why does it sound like

44
00:03:43,056 --> 00:03:44,766
you're annoyed and angry now?

45
00:03:45,391 --> 00:03:46,601
There you go.

46
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:49,395
I'm just explaining.

47
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:54,025
But I really came here to apologize.

48
00:03:54,108 --> 00:03:56,736
Because I realized that I should've been

49
00:03:56,819 --> 00:04:00,740
more patient and understanding
of your situation.

50
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:05,286
Because I've experienced before
what you're going through now.

51
00:04:07,956 --> 00:04:09,249
Having feelings for Alex?

52
00:04:09,332 --> 00:04:10,667
No!

53
00:04:11,417 --> 00:04:13,127
What I mean to say is,

54
00:04:13,711 --> 00:04:16,881
we're both in love

55
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:19,133
with someone who didn't reciprocate.

56
00:04:20,176 --> 00:04:21,511
Me?

57
00:04:22,553 --> 00:04:23,846
That's not me, okay?

58
00:04:24,514 --> 00:04:25,556
That's not me.

59
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:33,690
You know, I was thinking,
while Donatello is still peeing,

60
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:36,776
why don't we settle this standoff of ours?

61
00:04:36,859 --> 00:04:39,279
You know, so we can be efficient.

62
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:48,121
Oh, Agent Alex.

63
00:04:58,881 --> 00:05:00,008
Donatello?

64
00:05:06,973 --> 00:05:07,807
Quickly!

65
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:09,100
Okay.

66
00:05:09,183 --> 00:05:10,310
- Coming.
- Straight ahead.

67
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:21,904
I have a sharp memory,

68
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:23,906
and it hasn't been a while

69
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:28,453
since you made that heartfelt confession
to Agent Alex.

70
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:34,250
I don't even know what I liked about her.

71
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:37,545
Love is really complicated.

72
00:05:37,628 --> 00:05:40,214
It can completely break your standards.

73
00:05:40,298 --> 00:05:42,175
Even when you least expect it.

74
00:05:42,258 --> 00:05:45,136
Your heart just suddenly starts beating.

75
00:05:45,678 --> 00:05:48,473
You suddenly fall for someone
you never expected.

76
00:05:48,556 --> 00:05:50,433
And one day you'll realize

77
00:05:52,268 --> 00:05:54,228
you've developed feelings for them.

78
00:05:57,356 --> 00:05:58,483
Walk.

79
00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:01,903
Faster!

80
00:06:06,741 --> 00:06:07,992
Stay right there.

81
00:06:23,049 --> 00:06:27,512
I think I get why you're
attracted to Agent Alex.

82
00:06:28,513 --> 00:06:33,893
- Why?
- Because you're both falling for someone

83
00:06:33,976 --> 00:06:36,771
who can't return your affection.

84
00:06:38,731 --> 00:06:42,026
But I admire your courage.

85
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:45,113
Not everyone can confess,

86
00:06:45,196 --> 00:06:47,990
not everyone can take that first step,

87
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:52,370
and what people ultimately look for
in a relationship is something lasting,

88
00:06:52,453 --> 00:06:54,580
like… friendship.

89
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:56,415
And you,

90
00:06:57,166 --> 00:07:00,753
you've already told Agent Alex
how important she is to you.

91
00:07:00,837 --> 00:07:04,340
So now you already exist in her orbit,

92
00:07:04,423 --> 00:07:06,259
as more than just a friend.

93
00:07:35,705 --> 00:07:37,039
I don't have a gun.

94
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:19,248
Wait, time out!

95
00:08:30,009 --> 00:08:31,219
- Mikoy!
- Mikoy!

96
00:08:37,808 --> 00:08:40,353
Sweetheart, why did you
put your face in the way?

97
00:08:41,854 --> 00:08:43,439
We need to leave.

98
00:08:44,273 --> 00:08:45,650
You can't leave.

99
00:08:45,733 --> 00:08:47,485
Alex, I'm not lying to you.

100
00:08:47,568 --> 00:08:50,029
I'm telling the truth that Chiara
is no longer a Moraviano.

101
00:08:56,410 --> 00:08:57,703
Alex, come on.

102
00:08:57,787 --> 00:08:59,872
Let's talk this through first.

103
00:09:35,491 --> 00:09:37,577
Clear! Move, move, move, move!

104
00:10:19,327 --> 00:10:20,411
Wait, wait.

105
00:10:20,494 --> 00:10:22,079
Who were you talking to
through your earpiece?

106
00:10:22,163 --> 00:10:23,456
You have backup?

107
00:10:26,542 --> 00:10:28,878
That's why I brought guns,
not just one, but two.

108
00:10:41,515 --> 00:10:45,019
As a matter of fact,
they gave me their full support.

109
00:10:45,102 --> 00:10:48,397
There's a tactical squad positioned
right outside this room.

110
00:10:48,939 --> 00:10:50,733
So you have nowhere to run.

111
00:11:12,713 --> 00:11:14,507
<i>I admire your courage.</i>

112
00:11:17,093 --> 00:11:20,554
<i>You told Agent Alex</i>
<i>how important she is to you.</i>

113
00:11:20,638 --> 00:11:24,100
<i>So now you exist in her orbit,</i>

114
00:11:24,183 --> 00:11:26,227
<i>as more than just friends.</i>

115
00:11:37,446 --> 00:11:38,948
There's an update from Agent Alex.

116
00:11:43,744 --> 00:11:44,662
‪Hold on.

117
00:11:45,329 --> 00:11:46,372
Here it is.

118
00:11:48,624 --> 00:11:50,292
Donatello escaped.

119
00:11:51,043 --> 00:11:53,170
You are my targets.

120
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:59,593
Arresting Il Pittore
would just be a bonus.

121
00:12:05,558 --> 00:12:06,976
Now tell me.

122
00:12:13,023 --> 00:12:14,900
Because we can help you.

123
00:12:16,610 --> 00:12:19,738
Chiara and I can help you

124
00:12:19,822 --> 00:12:22,158
bring down the real villains
of this story.

125
00:12:24,535 --> 00:12:27,663
It's La Morte Bianca and the Concordat.

126
00:12:38,215 --> 00:12:40,426
I wouldn't be asking if I had.

127
00:13:58,671 --> 00:13:59,713
- Actually.
- True.

128
00:13:59,797 --> 00:14:01,382
Or maybe an influencer?

129
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:07,429
What did she say?

130
00:14:07,513 --> 00:14:09,014
I didn't understand either.

131
00:14:09,098 --> 00:14:10,849
You know what? I'll just go
catch up with our tricycle.

132
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:12,643
Let's go!

133
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:26,532
Sorry, madam.

134
00:14:39,920 --> 00:14:42,214
- Here are the snacks.
- Are you sure you don't need help?

135
00:14:42,298 --> 00:14:45,593
You sit down. You're our guests.

136
00:14:45,676 --> 00:14:46,802
I'll take care of it.

137
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:49,680
- Okay.
- Our rice cakes.

138
00:14:49,763 --> 00:14:51,348
Put those down, Betchay.

139
00:14:52,641 --> 00:14:55,352
Wow, so this is what it's like
in the province?

140
00:14:55,436 --> 00:14:58,397
You have snacks together
and everyone joins in.

141
00:14:58,480 --> 00:15:00,316
Of course.

142
00:15:02,401 --> 00:15:04,278
Like they always say, right?

143
00:15:04,987 --> 00:15:05,905
I see.

144
00:15:05,988 --> 00:15:09,992
I thought people only ate
when they felt dizzy or had a headache.

145
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:14,288
Oh my, Berto, did you hear
what your daughter just said?

146
00:15:14,371 --> 00:15:16,790
Are you taking care of her properly?

147
00:15:16,874 --> 00:15:20,502
Oh. No, no, it's not Dad Sir.
I'm the one with the problem.

148
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:24,131
Even Sofie needs to eat
at the proper time.

149
00:15:25,132 --> 00:15:26,258
Roger that.

150
00:15:28,135 --> 00:15:30,304
What a small world, huh?

151
00:15:30,387 --> 00:15:35,309
Imagine, you turned out to be the parents
of Sofie's FUBU.

152
00:15:37,102 --> 00:15:38,187
What's a FUBU?

153
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:41,398
It means fun buddy, Mom.
Fun buddy is what it means.

154
00:15:41,482 --> 00:15:42,524
Okay.

155
00:15:44,026 --> 00:15:45,653
Didn't you tell me before?

156
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:47,780
I can't remember anymore.

157
00:15:47,863 --> 00:15:50,866
Anyway, it means something like,

158
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:53,160
you started out as friends.

159
00:15:54,036 --> 00:15:56,664
Like Mario and me back then.
We were FUBUs too.

160
00:15:57,373 --> 00:16:00,834
Daddy Sir, that's an old term,
and it's not cool these days.

161
00:16:03,796 --> 00:16:04,797
All right.

162
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,548
You said it.

163
00:16:06,632 --> 00:16:13,013
Well, all I wanted to say is that
Mario and I…

164
00:16:18,394 --> 00:16:20,521
You and Dad were best friends?

165
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:28,988
We were best friends.

166
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:30,739
Back then.

167
00:16:32,574 --> 00:16:35,995
But then, we got busy with our own lives.

168
00:16:36,787 --> 00:16:39,039
We lost communication, so…

169
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:57,558
There you go again with your excuses.

170
00:16:58,809 --> 00:17:02,896
Well, we applied to the military together.

171
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:04,732
But Mario here

172
00:17:04,815 --> 00:17:08,444
decided to walk away from it
because he felt

173
00:17:09,028 --> 00:17:12,406
that it wasn't the life for him.

174
00:17:13,073 --> 00:17:16,326
I left because I wanted to start a family.

175
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:24,418
So if you've known each other that long,

176
00:17:27,254 --> 00:17:30,924
So, was she his first great love?

177
00:17:37,973 --> 00:17:42,144
Here's your order. Thank you and enjoy!

178
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:45,314
Tess.

179
00:17:46,774 --> 00:17:48,901
Look at Berto Butete.

180
00:17:48,984 --> 00:17:51,153
He's been staring at you for a while now.

181
00:17:51,236 --> 00:17:53,989
Looks like he really likes you.

182
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:56,950
Looks like you're the one who likes him.

183
00:17:57,034 --> 00:17:58,410
I don't like him.

184
00:17:58,494 --> 00:18:00,204
The one I really like

185
00:18:00,788 --> 00:18:03,207
is the guy coming in yellow!

186
00:18:07,836 --> 00:18:10,089
You're being too harsh on Berto!

187
00:18:12,466 --> 00:18:15,719
- Bro!
- Bro!

188
00:18:20,307 --> 00:18:22,351
- Oh, you!
- You look expensive, bro!

189
00:18:22,434 --> 00:18:23,727
You really are something!

190
00:18:23,811 --> 00:18:25,020
I know your type.

191
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:28,565
The rough-and-tough kind!

192
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:31,819
Listen to that mouth of yours!

193
00:18:31,902 --> 00:18:32,945
Why?

194
00:18:33,028 --> 00:18:35,739
The kind who roughs up bad people.

195
00:18:36,365 --> 00:18:38,283
Oh, stop it!

196
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:41,161
Fine, Catacutan is all yours.

197
00:18:41,245 --> 00:18:43,831
So, Berto is for me!

198
00:18:45,582 --> 00:18:47,376
Because I really feel like

199
00:18:48,001 --> 00:18:51,839
he's the meringue on top of my--

200
00:18:51,922 --> 00:18:54,216
That better not be something naughty!

201
00:18:54,299 --> 00:18:56,093
My bread roll!

202
00:18:56,176 --> 00:18:57,261
Okay.

203
00:19:04,643 --> 00:19:06,645
He winked at me!

204
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:16,071
Mom, you're spacing out.

205
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:18,240
Are you having flashbacks?

206
00:19:18,323 --> 00:19:21,577
No, dear. You know,
I was just reminiscing.

207
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:23,871
I remembered Maya.

208
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:29,543
You know, dear,

209
00:19:30,043 --> 00:19:35,007
Maya was one of the kindest people
I've ever met in this world.

210
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:40,429
I wish I had met her too.

211
00:19:42,514 --> 00:19:46,476
My Mom died while giving birth to me.

212
00:19:51,481 --> 00:19:56,737
But for now, of course, I want
to hear stories about her.

213
00:20:10,417 --> 00:20:12,753
Mikoy, is what she said
about the Concordat true?

214
00:20:13,337 --> 00:20:15,923
That there's an even bigger group
than the Moravianos?

215
00:20:20,135 --> 00:20:21,887
Mikoy, answer me.

216
00:20:24,181 --> 00:20:25,307
Hold on.

217
00:20:25,807 --> 00:20:27,559
Why are you looking at Mikoy?

218
00:20:27,643 --> 00:20:29,311
Why are you only asking him?

219
00:20:31,438 --> 00:20:33,440
Do you think I'm a liar and he's not?

220
00:20:35,901 --> 00:20:39,529
And after all the lies you've told
to protect your family

221
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:41,323
and the Moravianos,

222
00:20:41,406 --> 00:20:42,908
how can I trust you?

223
00:20:42,991 --> 00:20:44,326
Wait, wait.

224
00:20:45,661 --> 00:20:48,538
But to be fair, Agent Alex, same with me.

225
00:20:48,622 --> 00:20:50,207
I can lie as well.

226
00:20:51,291 --> 00:20:52,125
Go ahead.

227
00:20:56,838 --> 00:20:58,215
Alex.

228
00:20:58,298 --> 00:21:00,008
I'm not mad at you

229
00:21:00,092 --> 00:21:01,468
because I already know

230
00:21:02,052 --> 00:21:04,346
that you have feelings for me.

231
00:21:06,515 --> 00:21:09,268
You just don't know how I feel

232
00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:12,187
when I'm with you.

233
00:21:22,781 --> 00:21:24,992
Darn it! Let me try again.

234
00:21:25,075 --> 00:21:27,286
Please, Mikoy, don't you dare.

235
00:21:29,871 --> 00:21:32,916
Besides, that's not helping
your situation with Chiara.

236
00:21:37,629 --> 00:21:39,381
Who is La Morte Bianca?

237
00:21:40,590 --> 00:21:42,843
Yes! Of course she is.

238
00:21:43,427 --> 00:21:45,804
Isn't she just a fictional mafia character

239
00:21:45,887 --> 00:21:48,890
created to give the illusion
of fear and discipline?

240
00:21:49,516 --> 00:21:51,101
Nope. She's absolutely real.

241
00:21:51,184 --> 00:21:53,312
Well, I've never met her face-to-face.

242
00:21:53,395 --> 00:21:55,439
I haven't even met her online.

243
00:21:55,522 --> 00:21:58,483
But after Chiara and I came clean
about all our secrets,

244
00:21:58,567 --> 00:22:00,277
she told me everything,

245
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:01,695
and I mean everything.

246
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:03,697
Her entire backstory,

247
00:22:03,780 --> 00:22:05,949
including La Morte Bianca.

248
00:22:09,745 --> 00:22:12,456
She even told me about
her erogenous zones.

249
00:22:14,166 --> 00:22:15,459
That's SPG.

250
00:22:15,542 --> 00:22:16,501
Right, right.

251
00:22:16,585 --> 00:22:17,961
But she's really real.

252
00:22:18,045 --> 00:22:21,548
If we thought before that the Moravianos
were our only enemies,

253
00:22:21,631 --> 00:22:22,924
we were very wrong.

254
00:22:23,008 --> 00:22:24,176
There's something worse.

255
00:22:24,801 --> 00:22:28,305
There's a bigger force that is about
to descend upon the entire Philippines.

256
00:22:57,876 --> 00:23:02,714
You want protection for yourself,
for Mikoy, and for your family, right?

257
00:23:29,449 --> 00:23:31,660
Oh no! My gosh!
This brownout is ridiculous.

258
00:23:33,370 --> 00:23:34,621
No warning at all.

259
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:36,832
But that's how it is, darling.

260
00:23:39,167 --> 00:23:41,837
You see, during summer,

261
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:44,256
it gets hot, so everyone ends up
using their air conditioners at once.

262
00:23:44,339 --> 00:23:45,882
The power grid can't handle it.

263
00:23:45,966 --> 00:23:50,137
And then,
we end up with a rotating brownout.

264
00:24:32,220 --> 00:24:33,930
Why don't you first prove to me

265
00:24:34,014 --> 00:24:35,807
that the information you're offering
is valuable?

266
00:24:35,891 --> 00:24:36,975
Then I'll decide

267
00:24:37,058 --> 00:24:39,769
<i>whether it's truly worthy</i>
<i>of immunity from prosecution.</i>

268
00:24:41,563 --> 00:24:43,440
You need vital information, right?

269
00:24:43,523 --> 00:24:44,608
I can give that.

270
00:24:44,691 --> 00:24:46,276
But this is a game changer.

271
00:24:46,359 --> 00:24:47,652
Make sure you're ready.

272
00:24:48,486 --> 00:24:49,529
Why are you here?

273
00:24:49,613 --> 00:24:50,989
Is it an urgent matter?

274
00:24:52,699 --> 00:24:55,202
G.A.G.O. has called an emergency meeting.

275
00:24:55,869 --> 00:24:56,953
About what?

276
00:24:57,037 --> 00:24:58,914
<i>For the case of the Moraviano.</i>

277
00:25:04,502 --> 00:25:07,339
With all this long presentation,

278
00:25:07,422 --> 00:25:10,926
and you just asked me
to protect this couple,

279
00:25:11,009 --> 00:25:12,594
Chiara and Mikoy?
